HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1467
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor Shannon Roddy, Mountain Education
Foundation Middle School Educator of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those outstanding
professionals who have devoted their careers to providing the highest quality education for
Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Shannon Roddy, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Shannon Roddy has been selected as the Middle School Educator of the
Year by the Mountain Education Foundation, a most befitting honor that recognizes her
dedication as an instructor and mentor; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Roddy is an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike, and her
friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Shannon Roddy truly epitomizes the ideal of the dedicated professional who
is wholly committed to the highest precepts of public service and quality education for all, and
she should be specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Shannon Roddy on being chosen as Middle
School Educator of the Year by the Mountain Education Foundation, commend her exceptional
service to the good people of Tennessee, salute her professional expertise and personal
excellence, and wish her all the best in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
